attributes.additional_details: This bill is opposed by the Refugee Council, which has said "The plans won’t stop the crossings but will simply leave traumatised people locked up in a state of misery being treated as criminals and suspected terrorists without a fair hearing on our soil."
attributes.background: Simply, do not allow this bill to become law! We believe this bill, that would permanently ban illegal immigrants from re-entering the UK and applying for British citizenship, is draconian and will not fulfil its purpose of stopping boats from crossing the Channel.
